<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Bounty quests are given by the Beastmaster. There are Beastmasters in Lothlorien and Minas Anor. <p>
Some quests are trickier than you might think. For example, there are <em>two</em> types of some monsters (e.g. novice rangers). One type appears as a solitary monster, the other appears in groups. The corpse of one kind cannot be substituted for the other in a bounty quest. 
</p>
<p>
Some other quests are very difficult due to monster rarity or monster level. A difficult quest is a random occurence; you are not being picked on. The reward is valuable to some characters, and if you want it, you need to earn it. 
</p>
<p>
To fulfill a bounty quest, bring the requested corpse (or hacked meat of it) back to the Beastmaster. Speak to the Beastmaster a second time to obtain a new quest. 
</p>
<p>
Bounty monsters are randomly chosen, but they're (loosely) based on your experience level.  The following types of monsters are <em>ineligible</em> for selection: uniques, corpse-less monsters, specially generated monsters, monsters that are automatically pets or friendly, breeders, joke monsters, and good monsters.  Anything else is fair game. 
</p>
<p>
The reward: If you don't yet know the Monster-lore skill, you will be taught it (with multiplier 0.900). If you don't yet know the Corpse-preservation skill, you will be taught it (with multiplier 0.800). You will also be given one skill point in Monster-lore for each corpse returned. 
</p>
<p>
Note: This quest was changed in ToME 2.0.0, previous versions had a different quest. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Things I don't recall immediately (please delete as you correct it): 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Is there a max # of quests? I think so, but I don't recall how many.   
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
<a href="./ReenenLaurie">ReenenLaurie</a>: I don't think there's a max, but most classes has +0.500 so completing 100 quests may take a while. 
</p>
<p>
(some newbie) : What are the odds of a monster dropping a corpse in relation to your Corpse-preservation skill. I tried a Bounty Quest at 0 in it and none of the 15 or so Large white snake dropped one. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./FearofFours">FearofFours</a></strong>: See <a href="./www.killerbunnies.org/angband/skill-230.html#preserv">http://www.killerbunnies.org/angband/skill-230.html#preserv</a> for more, but basically, it's a 10% chance with skill at 0. You were perhaps a tad unlucky. Keep trying. 
</p>
